As the last true liberal, I have to note that the Anglo-liberal tradition walked us into a game of prisoner's dilemma in which the competitor gets to defect at will while we beat ourselves up if we do. There's only one way that game ends, and it's collapse of the game. We're here.
If you can restrain yourself from going full cosmo-shitlib about it.
... Half constitutional originalism and half revolutionary wokism isn't in fact half-and-half. It's half draw, half loss, indefinitely reiterated.
Acceptable.
Say what you like about Singapore, at least they're grappling with the real problem.
Liberal, but strictly neutral about whether liberalism wins or not, isn't a stable equilibrium.
Upward.

Between (true) conservatism and liberalism, 'liberalism wins half the time' is moderated liberalism.
Between leftism and liberalism, 'liberalism wins half the time' is inexorable leftism. 
Anglo-liberals have been catastrophically slow to recognize this.
... Deliberately confusing US political nomenclature, in which illiberal leftism is popularly known as liberalism, definitely hasn't helped.
